 Port Elizabeth - Although the Port Elizabeth Airport only received 15.6mm, other areas of the city received above 25mm of rain overnight, the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service said on Monday. "Over the city’s main catchment area between 13 and 30mm was measured," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. "Other noteworthy figures were Plettenberg Bay at 34.6mm and George at 29.4mm. "The drought ravaged area of Graaf Reinett only had 6.2mm and areas around Adelaide had 8mm." Sampson still said that the public must continue to use water sparingly as the forecast is for below normal rainfall up to December. Station Names 30 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 15.6 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 23.0 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 18.6 AWSH Chatty 17.8 AWS Coega 15.4 AWSH Fettes Road 20.6 ARS Flower Reserve 19.8 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 26.4 ARS St Albans 26.6 AWS Uitenhage 10.0 Man Woodridge 20.1 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 13.0 ARS Kareedouw 26.4 Man Kareedouw 31.0 Man Kouga Dam 30.0 AWS Patensie 18.0 Man Swartkops  * Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo 25.2 AWS Bisho/KWT 18.2 AWS Cape St Francis 25.6 AWS Cradock 6.2 AWS East London 18.6 AWS Fort Beaufort 8.2 AWS George 29.4 AWS Graaff Reinet 6.2 AWS Grahamstown 13.0 AWS Henry`s Flats 6.4 AWS Joubertina 13.0 AWS Mossel Bay 21.6 AWS Mthatha 1.4 AWS Plettenberg bay 34.6 AWS Port Alfred 3.2 AWS Queenstown 4.6  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 